  <p class="ref">[EN 1992-1-1 (5.38)]</p>
  <p>
   <b>Check if biaxial bending design is required</b>
  </p>
  <p>
   <span class="eq">
    <span class="dvc">
     <var>λ</var>
     <sub>y</sub>
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     <var>λ</var>
     <sub>z</sub>
    </span>
    =
    <span class="dvc">
     46.19
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     19.79
    </span>
    = 2.33
   </span>
   &gt; 2
  </p>
  <p>
   <span class="eq">
    <span class="dvc">
     <var>e</var>
     <sub>y</sub>
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     <var>h</var>
    </span>
    ·
    <span class="dvc">
     <var>b</var>
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     <var>e</var>
     <sub>z</sub>
    </span>
    =
    <span class="dvc">
     201.84
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     700
    </span>
    ·
    <span class="dvc">
     300
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     41.67
    </span>
    = 2.08
   </span>
   &gt; 0.2 and
   <span class="eq">
    <span class="dvc">
     <var>e</var>
     <sub>z</sub>
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     <var>b</var>
    </span>
    ·
    <span class="dvc">
     <var>h</var>
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     <var>e</var>
     <sub>y</sub>
    </span>
    =
    <span class="dvc">
     41.67
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     300
    </span>
    ·
    <span class="dvc">
     700
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     201.84
    </span>
    = 0.482
   </span>
   &gt; 0.2
  </p>
  <p>The condition is NOT satisfied. Biaxial bending design is required.</p>
  <p>
   Ultimate axial force resistance-
   <span class="eq">
    <var>N</var>
    <sub>Rd</sub>
    =
    <var>N</var>
    <sub>Rd_max</sub>
    = 3020
   </span>
   kN
  </p>
  <p>
   <span class="eq">
    <span class="dvc">
     <var>N</var>
     <sub>Ed</sub>
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     <var>N</var>
     <sub>Rd</sub>
    </span>
    =
    <span class="dvc">
     1200
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     3020
    </span>
    = 0.397
   </span>
  </p>
  <p>
   Calculation of the exponent factor
   <i>a</i>
  </p>
  <p>
   <span class="eq">
    <var>a</var>
    = 1 +
    <span class="b1">(</span>
    <span class="dvc">
     <var>N</var>
     <sub>Ed</sub>
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     <var>N</var>
     <sub>Rd</sub>
    </span>
    − 0.1
    <span class="b1">)</span>
    · 0.833 = 1 +
    <span class="b1">(</span>
    <span class="dvc">
     1200
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     3020
    </span>
    − 0.1
    <span class="b1">)</span>
    · 0.833 = 1.25
   </span>
  </p>
  <p class="ref">[EN 1992-1-1 (5.39)]</p>
  <p>
   <b>Biaxial bending check</b>
  </p>
  <p>
   <span class="eq">
    <var>k</var>
    =
    <span class="b1">(</span>
    <span class="dvc">
     <var>M</var>
     <sub>Edz</sub>
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     <var>M</var>
     <sub>Rdz</sub>
    </span>
    <span class="b1">)</span>
    <sup class="raised">
     <var>a</var>
    </sup>
    +
    <span class="b1">(</span>
    <span class="dvc">
     <var>M</var>
     <sub>Edy</sub>
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     <var>M</var>
     <sub>Rdy</sub>
    </span>
    <span class="b1">)</span>
    <sup class="raised">
     <var>a</var>
    </sup>
    =
    <span class="b1">(</span>
    <span class="dvc">
     242.2
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     398.62
    </span>
    <span class="b1">)</span>
    <sup class="raised">1.25</sup>
    +
    <span class="b1">(</span>
    <span class="dvc">
     50
     <span class="dvl">
     </span>
     100
    </span>
    <span class="b1">)</span>
    <sup class="raised">1.25</sup>
    = 0.958
   </span>
  </p>
  <p>
   (
   <i>M</i>
   <sub>Edz</sub>
   /
   <i>M</i>
   <sub>Rdz</sub>
   )
   <sup>a</sup>
   + (
   <i>M</i>
   <sub>Edy</sub>
   /
   <i>M</i>
   <sub>Rdy</sub>
   )
   <sup>a</sup>
   ≤ 1. The design check is satisfied.
  </p>
